# Financial Risk Market Stress Testing Precious Metal Scenarios Amount

## identifier
de8066

## type
float

## definition
This is the value, as at the relevant date, of the effect on positions in precious metals due to movements in prices and volatilities as specified in stress testing scenarios. This represents the change in the portfolio value of these positions given stress testing scenarios applied.

All positions in gold and other precious metals (including silver, platinum and palladium) must be included in the stress test portfolio revaluations.

For the purposes of this item, in assessing the change in portfolio value, positions in the same precious metal, but with differing maturities, may be netted.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=FinancialRisk.Market.StressTestingPreciousMetalScenarios.Amount
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.06
- period=instant
